✅ Task 2: Explore All Given Git Commands Locally & Remotely
1. Git Commands
✔ Check Git Version
git --version

✔ Configure Git User
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"

✔ View All Git Configurations
git config --list

2. Repository Management
✔ Initialize Repository
git init

✔ Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git

✔ View Remote Repositories
git remote -v

✔ Add a Remote
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repository.git

✔ Push Changes to Remote
git push <remote_name> <branch_name>
git push origin main

✔ Pull Updates from Remote
git pull <remote_name> <branch_name>
git pull origin main

✔ Remove a Remote
git remote remove origin

✔ Rename a Remote
git remote rename origin upstream

✔ Fetch Updates Without Merge
git fetch <remote_name>

✔ Change Remote URL
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/username/new-repository.git

✔ View Remote Info
git remote show origin

3. Staging & Committing
✔ Check Status
git status

✔ Add Files
git add filename.txt
git add .

✔ Commit Changes
git commit -m "Commit message"

4. Branching & Merging
✔ Branch Commands
git branch              # list branches
git branch -a           # list all (local + remote)
git branch branch-name  # create branch
git branch -d branch    # delete branch
git branch -D branch    # force delete

✔ List Remote Branches
git branch -r

✔ Checkout Branches
git checkout branch-name
git checkout -b new-branch

✔ Remove Deleted Remote Branches
git remote prune origin

✔ Fetch a Specific Branch
git fetch origin feature-branch

✔ Set Upstream Branch
git push --set-upstream origin feature-branch

✔ Merge Branches
git checkout main
git merge branch-name

✔ Rebase Onto Remote Branch
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main

5. Undoing Changes
✔ Unstage a File
git reset <file>

✔ Revert a Commit
git revert <commit>

6. Viewing History
✔ View Commit History
git log
git log --oneline

✔ View Differences
git diff

✔ View a Specific Commit
git show <commit>

7. Undo file changes before staging
git restore filename

8. Correct Wrong Commit Message
git commit --amend -m "Corrected commit message"

9. Recover Deleted Branch
git reflog
git checkout -b feature-ui <commit_hash>

10. Download Updates Without Merge
git fetch origin

11. Remove Sensitive File from Git History
git filter-branch --force --index-filter \
"git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch secrets.txt" \
--prune-empty --tag-name-filter cat -- --all

12. Merge Another Branch into Current
git checkout previous-branch
git merge another-branch

13. Manual Merge Conflict Resolution

Open file (e.g., x.js)

