Then run:

git add app.js
git commit

14. .gitignore
✔ Create File
touch .gitignore

✔ Common Rules
*.log
secret_file.txt
temp/
folder/*
!folder/important_file.txt
*.bak

15. See Who Changed Each Line
git blame script.py

16. Git Stash
git stash
git switch another-branch
git switch main
git stash apply

17. Check If Branch Is Merged
git branch --merged

18. Delete Multiple Local Branches
git branch -d branch1 branch2 branch3

⭐ OUTPUTS:

Students must provide screenshots of:
• branch creation
• switching
• commit logs
• merge results
• conflict resolution
• stash usage
• remote changes
• push/pull/fetch
• reflog & branch recovery
